<br>
I thought i would make a post on this topic, because it can be a little confusing.<br>
<br>
As enchanters, we get access to A variety of &quot;Root&quot; type spells.  They are NOT all the same.  I did extensive research on this topic when i was a shaman, trying to figure out when to use what spell.  <br>
<br>
First off :<br>
<br>
All Root spells are not in the same line.<br>
<br>
You would THINK that all the root spells are in the same line of spells, but they arent.  Following is a description of the root spells :<br>
<br>
1) ROOT<br>
<br>
Level 8 Enchanter spell<br>
Mana cost : 30 mana<br>
Casting time : 2 seconds<br>
Maximum Root Duration = 48 seconds<br>
Recast : instant<br>
<br>
2) *** Enstill<br>
<br>
Level 29 Enchanter spell<br>
Mana Cost : 60 mana<br>
Casting time 2.5 Seconds<br>
Maximum duration = 96 seconds<br>
Recast : instant<br>
<br>
3) Immobilize <br>
<br>
level 39 Enchanter spell<br>
Mana Cost 80 mana<br>
Casting time 1.75 seconds<br>
Maximum duration : 60 seconds<br>
Recast (casters realm says 3 sec but i dont think its that long)<br>
<br>
4)***Paralyzing Earth<br>
<br>
Level 49 Enchanter spell<br>
Mana cost : 100 mana<br>
Casting time 2.5 seconds<br>
Maximum duration : 3 minutes<br>
Recast time ( again casters realm says 2.5 sec but doesnt seem that long )<br>
<br>
5)Fetter<br>
<br>
Level 58 Enchanter spell<br>
mana cost :75 mana<br>
Casting time 1.75 seconds<br>
Maximum duration : 3 minutes<br>
Recast : instant<br>
<br>
Ok , There they are.  You might be wondering why not just move from one to the other, as you level.  The reason is because there are 2 distinct lines of roots. I will call them the &quot;combat&quot; root line and the &quot; root parking &quot; root line.  Spells in the combat root line :<br>
<br>
1) Root<br>
2)Immobilize<br>
3) Fetter<br>
<br>
Spells in the &quot;Root parking&quot; line :<br>
<br>
1) Enstill<br>
2) Paralizing earth<br>
3) Fetter<br>
<br>
What is the difference ?  Spells in the &quot;Combat&quot; root line cast fast, and have a slightly lower resist rate.  They dont last as long as the &quot;root parking&quot; line, but bashing mobs has a tendancy to break roots anyway, as will nuking.  The &quot;combat&quot; root line of spells is for rooting mobs for a short time, when you expect that mob to be taking melee / nuking damage shortly.  It is also for when you are trying to keep the mob in one place because it is frenzied on you.  The slightly lower resist rate means that this line of spells should stick slightly more often, and last a little bit longer, when the mob is being meleed ( bashed ).<br>
<br>
The &quot; Root Parking line of spells :<br>
<br>
1) Enstill<br>
2) Paralyzing Earth<br>
3) Fetter<br>
<br>
Is the line of spells you use when you need root to last a LONG time, AND the mob is not going to be taking any melee / nuking damage.  This line of spells is great for root parking.  The mob has a slightly higher chance of breaking root when it is bashed / nuked with this line of spells.  This set of roots ( with the exception of fetter ), also cast slower, making them in appropriate for &quot;combat&quot; rooting when you need to Flux  / Root.  <br>
<br>
Use this line of spells anyplace where Mobs CANT be mezzed, but you still need to crowd control them by root parking.  Places like Giant Class (flagged) mobs, The hole (deeper in), or lots of places in SoV where Mezz doesnt work.  For this line of spells to be most effective, you should tash your target first, pull it aside, root it, and leave it alone. No dots, No DD, No melee.. just leave it there.<br>
<br>
Contrast that with the other line of spells, which is made for use in everyday combat (faster casting times, slightly better resist rates, lower max duration).<br>
<br>
Fetter is an exception spell in all cases.  It is Fast casting, has the resist rate of the &quot;Combat&quot; class roots like root and immobilize, BUT it has the potential duration of the &quot; parking &quot; class roots like Enstill and paralyzing earth.  Fetter is in all cases an upgrade to ALL of the roots.<br>
<br>
In conclusion, the upgrade paths for this line of spells is :<br>
<br>
Root<br>
Immobilize<br>
Fetter<br>
<br>
Or <br>
<br>
Enstill<br>
paralyzing earth<br>
Fetter<br>
<br>
Use the first group for combat, and the second one for parking.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Root&quot; works actually in most of the cases where you need to root in combat, i just choose to use &quot;immobilize&quot; instead of &quot;root&quot; for fast cast times.  That is a personal choice, and many , many enchanters use plain old root 90 percent of the time.  I personally only use the second line of spells in very personalized circumstances, where i KNOW i will be root parking ( going to Kael or some such).<br>
<br>
Hope this helps.<br>
<br>
Llorian<br>
55 Enchanter<br>
